00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:30,960
And then we'll schedule a next onboarding meeting that brings in the postdoc or the

155
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:38,440
RA that will be doing the image analysis in our team, where we can then guide the conversation

156
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:43,320
into even more specifics about the technical details of the project that are really relevant

157
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:51,320
to the person doing the image analysis, where then the, you know, sort of team lead or PI

158
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:56,360
level conversations, those expectations can be set in that first meeting.

159
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:10,040
Forms, we have all sorts of forms, and this can really help in the metadata component,

160
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:13,600
which I'm not going to start soapboxing about metadata.

161
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:17,160
You will find, I swear, I swear I'm not going to, I can resist.

162
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:20,800
You will find plenty of episodes where I do.

163
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:31,440
But handing off metadata along with the images is really, really important and is something

164
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:37,680
that is often a challenge or often forgotten, or things are handed in a way that is either

165
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:47,080
incomplete or the metadata that the collaborator is handing to us is not in the structure or

