00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:52,280
and an RA working on the blue task in parallel, because we need to get this done as quickly as

190
00:14:52,360 --> 00:15:01,000
possible. And it's okay to parallelize those. Or maybe, you know, maybe the priority isn't

191
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:06,200
speed. And so maybe we want to adjust this, like maybe it would be better to do the pink task first,

192
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:11,320
because we learned something about it and can make the blue task then better or easier or faster.

193
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:18,760
And so since the priority isn't speed, but quality, maybe we'll take a bit longer and move the blue

194
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:23,560
task just to after the pink task instead of at the same time. But setting it out like this

195
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:30,200
makes it can make it clear what can and can't be done at the same time, what needs to be given to

196
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:35,560
us so that we can reach goals and, you know, deliver them on time and just, you know, shared again,

197
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:41,560
all about setting shared expectations. But this is, I think, a really helpful tool for sort of

